AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - ASIA (30): CHINA, VIET NAM, CAMBODIA, DOMESTIC, SPREAD, FAO
*********************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 5 Apr 2019
Source: FAO [Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations]/EMPRES [Emergency Prevention System] - Animal Health: ASF situation in Asia update for 5 Apr 2019 [abridged, edited]
http://www.fao.org/ag/againfo/programmes/en/empres/ASF/Situation_update.html


Situation update [for the week 29 Mar to 5 Apr 2019]
[The next update will be issued on 12 Apr 2019].
------------------
China:
Since the China Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs (MARA) confirmed its 1st ASF outbreak in Liaoning Province on 3 Aug 2018, a total of 118 ASF outbreaks have been detected in 28 provinces/autonomous regions/municipalities. Around 1 million pigs have been culled in an effort to halt further spread.

- Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region: The 1st ASF outbreak occurred on one farming cooperative in Midong District, Urumqi City; 15 of 200 pigs became sick and died from the disease.

- Yunnan Province: ASF outbreak occurred in a village in Shangri-La City, Diqing Prefecture, Yunnan Province; 196 of 301 pigs became sick, of which 105 died.

- Hubei Province: ASF outbreak occurred on 2 farms in Lichuan City. A total of 8 of 142 pigs became sick on one farm, of which 5 died; on another farm, all 83 pigs became sick and 73 died.

Mongolia:
Since its 1st report on 15 Jan 2019, 11 outbreaks in 6 provinces and in Ulaanbaatar have been reported, involving 105 farms/households. More than 3115 pigs, more than 10% of the total pig population in Mongolia, have died/been destroyed due to the ASF outbreaks.

Viet Nam:
Since the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development (MARD) confirmed its ASF outbreaks on 19 Feb 2019, 23 provinces/cities reported outbreaks, and more than 89 600 pigs have been culled.

Cambodia:
The Ministry of Agriculture Forestry and Fisheries confirmed Cambodia's 1st ASF outbreak in a backyard farm in Saom Thum Commune, Ou Ya Dav District, Ratanakiri province. A total of 400 of 500 pigs died.

New actions undertaken during the week in China:

On 28 Mar 2019, a dried pork meat produced in Jiangsu Province was found in an illegal shipment, and a pork ham sausage produced in Heilongjiang Province that was in the possession of a passenger from Hong Kong SAR tested positive for ASF virus by the Hsinchu Airport Branch, Animal and Plant Health Inspection and Quarantine Bureau. The genomic sequence analysis of this virus showed 100% identity with ASF virus elsewhere in China.

--
Communicated by:
Juan Lubroth, DVM, PhD, ACVPM
Chief Veterinary Officer
Animal Health Service C-532
Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations
Rome, Italy

